notes for creating this app
step 1
download android studio
download flutter sdk
edit the environment for flutter sdk (note that no double flutter)
example in the env file
C:/src/flutter

step 2
connect to firebase with this command
npm install -g firebase-tools
this is to download node js and allow automatically download all the necessary things

firebase login
do firebase login

dart pub global activate flutterfire_cli
install this thing so that you can use flutterfire this command in terminal

flutterfire configure
configure your flutter project to firebase
this is to connect both of them
then you will get a list of project in firebase (make sure to create it first)
you need to choose which one you one

once done you will have a firebase_options.dart
it is a file with a lot of api key to connect to your project

next update your pubspec yaml with the dependencies that you need with the correct version and pub get
remember to also include the asset and image you need

go to your firebase
check for the id make sure it is correct
then download manually the google service json.
note that you should be include the google service json at same level at android=> app=>google-services.json

step 4
initialize the main
(learn all things about initialize)
create the sign up and login screen
create notification function and plugin

